    "Transfer learning overcomes this by leveraging knowledge acquired for one task to solve related ones, even if the learning crosses domains.",
    "It is specially popular in DL due to the need of large datasets.",
    "Together with transfer learning, new ways of obtaining additional data would be highly beneficial.",
    "Data augmentation is used to expand limited data by generating new samples from existing ones, i.e., synthetic data, and can be a powerful strategy to reduce overfitting and therefore improving the performance of DL models.",
    "It encompasses a suite of techniques that enhance the size and quality of training datasets (Shorten and Khoshgoftaar 2019)."
